  "texts": [
    "For this embedding, we haveK C = SO(2, C) ≃ C *.",
    "Let P → Σ be a holomorphic principal SO(2, C)-bundle.",
    "The group C * embeds into SL 2 (C) by a → diag(𝔭 C = 0 b c 0: b, c ∈ C ≃ C ⊗2 ⊕ (C *) ⊗2 as C * -modules.Here, C * acts on C ⊗k by the tensor product representation induced from the standard representation of C * on C (i.e.",
    "if we identify C ⊗k with C as a vector space, then a• v = a k v for a ∈ C *, v ∈ C ⊗k).",
    "Then, K Σ ⊗ (P × K C 𝔭 C) ≃ K Σ L 2 ⊕ K Σ L -2,where L is the line bundle associated to P via the standard representation of C * on C. Thus, an SL 2 (R)-Higgs bundle is a triple (L, β, γ) where L is a holomorphic line bundle, β ∈ H 0 (B, K Σ L 2), and γ ∈ H 0 (B, K Σ L -2).Recall that the degree of a complex vector bundle is given bydeg E = -1 2πi B tr Ω ∈ Z,where Ω is the curvature of any connection on E. An SL n (C)-Higgs bundle is called semistable if the associated vector bundle E satisfies deg E ′ ≤ 0, for all Φ-invariant subbundles E ′ ⊂ E. (Here, Φ-invariant means Φ(E ′) ⊂ K Σ ⊗ E ′.)"
